\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 1. M. pomifera} (Rafin.) C.K. Schneider, {\i Ill. Handb. Laubholzk. }{\b 1:} 806 (1906) ({\i M. aurantiaca} Nutt.). Tree. Leaves 5-12 cm, ovate, acuminate. Syncarp 10-14 cm in diameter, subglobose, orange. {\i Cultivated as a hedge plant and for ornament, and locally naturalized in S. Europe.} [It Rm Rs(K).] ({\i North America.})
