\pard\f0\fs28 Not spiny; leaves usually lobed; buds enclosed in the connate stipules. Stipules caducous, leaving a circular scar. Monoecious. Flowers enclosed within a fleshy urceolate structure. Stamens 4, straight in bud.
\par

