\pard\f0\fs28 {\b F. benghalensis} L.,{\i  Sp. Pl.} 1059 (1753), with massively spreading branches, an extensive system of prop-roots, and ovate, entire leaves, is grown as a shade tree in warmer parts of the Mediterranean region.
